                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/290.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister to Chile</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister of Foreign Affairs informs me that negotiations have been resumed with
                    Peru through intermediation of Chilean Consul at Callao and has shown to me
                    telegrams exchanged recently by which the effect of secret message of the
                    President of Peru to the Peruvian Congress which caused interruption of
                    negotiations is neutralized. From telegrams both parties appear anxious to reach
                    satisfactory arrangement but no definite propositions have been advanced.
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs hopes to settle on basis outlined in my despatch No.
                    300.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
